<item>
            <title>[HIVE-17825] Socket not closed when trying to read files to copy over in replication from metadata</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HIVE-17825</link>
                <project id="12310843" key="HIVE">Hive</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;for replication we create a _files in hdfs which lists the source files to be copied over for a table/partition. _files is read in ReplCopyTask to read what files to be copied. The File operations w.r.t to _files is not correct and we leave the files open there, which leads to a lot of CLOSE_WAIT connections to the source Data nodes from HS2 on the replica cluster.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
